12 (8) Establish a “resident bill of rights” for residents of assisted living
13 program facilities that includes, at a minimum:
14 (i) The right to be treated with consideration, respect, and full
15 recognition of human dignity and individuality;
16 (ii) The right to receive treatment, care, and services that are
17 adequate, appropriate, and in compliance with relevant federal and State laws, rules, and
18 regulations;
19 (iii) The right to be free from mental and physical abuse;
20 (iv) The right to be free from mental, verbal, sexual, and physical
21 abuse, neglect, or involuntary seclusion or exploitation;
22 (v) The right to notice, procedural fairness, and humane treatment
23 when being transferred or discharged from a facility;
24 (vi) The right to participate in decision making regarding transitions
25 in care, including a transfer or discharge from a facility;
26 (vii) The right to be free from physical and chemical restraints, except
27 for restraints that a physician authorizes for a clearly indicated medical need; and
28 (viii) The right to manage personal financial affairs;
